title: Panama spreads within Qld banana farm
text:
Thu, Aug 20, 2015, 5:58 PM AEST - Australia Markets closed Panama spreads within Qld banana farm AAP – 13 minutes ago Print 
A devastating fungal disease has spread within a far north Queensland banana farm. 
The Tully property was one of two properties quarantined earlier this year after testing positive to Panama TR4, a soil-borne fungus that attacks banana plants. 
While the other farm was eventually given the all-clear, biosecurity authorities confirmed on Thursday a separate area of the Tully farm had returned a positive sample for Panama. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Greece makes ECB repayment AFP
